Along the Southern Shore~
The Mirror-like Khelorn is slowly pulled to the northeast by a gentle current.
To the south a light forest descends a large hill to surround the lake, and to
The north you see a dark, forboding forest closing in.  As you stare into the
lake, you think you catch a momentary glimpse of something on the bottom, but
it is gone so quick you are left wondering if you really saw anything at all.
To the northwest lies the mouth of the river Khelorn, on its endless course of
plodding into the lake.
